aas:description.aas:langString: This aspect model is used to exchange manufacturing-oriented information of several parts, e.g. for quality tasks
A list of manufactured parts and their porperties
Manufacturing information for one part. Important properties are standardized. Besides that there is a key:value list to exchange further non-standardized properties for this part
The fully anonymous Catena-X ID of the manufactured part - only available after digital twin registry is fully operational
A unique quality task identifier where this manufacturing information belongs to. Optional to ensure that also data exchange without having a quality task.
Identifier assigned by the manufacturer for this specific part. In case of common parts: This identifier is not unique.
Serial part number given by the manufacturer. Not available for common parts.
Name of the manufactured part as given by the manufacturer.
Collection of defined manufacturing-related properties for this part
Date of manufacturing
Country code where the part was manufactured
Manufacturer-specific identifier of a the production plant of this part
Manufacturer-specific description of the production plant of this part
Manufacturer-specific batch identifier: In which batch was this part manufactured
On which production line was this part produced
Indicator whether this part was reworked during manufacturing
Number how often this part went through the EOL test
You can use this key:value list for additional properties that were not defined in this aspect model.
One key:value information pair
Key identifier for this additional information
Value for this additional information
